results.name: Arashio stable
results.intro:
Arashio stable is a stable of sumo wrestlers, part of the Tokitsukaze ichimon or group of stables. It was set up in June 2002 by former komusubi Ōyutaka, who branched off from Tokitsukaze stable. At the end of 2009 the stable produced its first sekitori, the Chinese born (but ethnic Mongolian) Sōkokurai who in 2013 returned to active sumo after a two-year absence when his dismissal for match-fixing was nullified by the courts. The stable is also home to the half-Japanese, half-Filipino wrestler Kōtokuzan. As of January 2020, the stable has eleven wrestlers. The stable's second sekitori, Wakatakakage, reached jūryō in May 2018.
Apart from its human residents, the Arashio was home to the cats Moru and Mugi, former strays which were adopted by the stable. Mugi died in 2019.
In March 2020 Sokokurai became the new Arashio Oyakata when his stablemaster reached the mandatory retirement age of 65.
